authentication-timeout.description: User can set the authentication timeout period of the SSH. By default, SSH authentication timeout interval is 60 seconds.

rekey-interval.description: User can set the interval for updating the key pair of the SSH server. By default, the interval for updating the key pair of the SSH server is 0 that indicates no updating.

keep-alive-enable.description: SSH server supports keep alive functionality will respond to client keep alive packets.

compatible-ssh1x.description: User can enable the earlier version-compatible function on the SSH server. By default, compatibility is enabled.

authentication-def.description: User can enable default authentication type as password on the SSH server.

auth-retries.description: User can set authentication retry times.

auth-bogus-mode.description: The bogus list of acceptable authentication 'method name' values makes it possible for the server to avoid disclosing information on which accounts exist.

sftp-max-user.description: User can configure maximum number of clients can be connected to server at any point of time for SFTP service.

scp-max-session.description: User can configure maximum number of clients can be connected to server at any point of time for SCP service.

src-ipv6-addr.description: SSH IPv6 server source IP address. The node /sshs:sshs/sshs:server/sshs:src-ipv6-addr is deprecated. You are advised to use the node /sshs:sshs/sshs:ipv6-server-sources/sshs:ipv6-server-source/sshs:src-ipv6-addr.

src-ipv6-vpn-name.description: SSH IPv6 server source VPN name. The node /sshs:sshs/sshs:server/sshs:src-ipv6-vpn-name is deprecated. You are advised to use the node /sshs:sshs/sshs:ipv6-server-sources/sshs:ipv6-server-source/sshs:src-ipv6-vpn-name.

src-interf-name.description: Specify the source interface name. The node /sshs:sshs/sshs:server/sshs:src-interf-name is deprecated. You are advised to use the node /sshs:sshs/sshs:ipv4-server-sources/sshs:ipv4-server-source/sshs:src-interface.

rsa-host-key.description: User can assign the rsa host key for rsa connection.

dsa-host-key.description: User can assign the dsa host key for dsa connection.

ecc-host-key.description: User can assign the ecc host key for ecc connection.

ipv4-acl-name.description: Server ACL name or number for IPv4 connections.

ipv4-acl-number.description: Server ACL number for IPv4 connections. The node /sshs:sshs/sshs:server/sshs:ipv4-acl-number is deprecated. You are advised to use the node /sshs:sshs/sshs:server/sshs:ipv4-acl-name.

ipv6-acl-name.description: Server ACL name or number for IPv6 connections.

ipv6-acl-number.description: Server ACL number for IPv6 connections. The node /sshs:sshs/sshs:server/sshs:ipv6-acl-number is deprecated. You are advised to use the node /sshs:sshs/sshs:server/sshs:ipv6-acl-name.

ssh-version.description: Indicates the SSH protocol version that the server supports. A version 1.99 can supports both protocol version 2.0 and protocol version 1.x, if the compatability is enabled.

rsa-server-key.description: User can assign the rsa server key for rsa connection.

name.description: User name is a string of characters without a blank space.

sftp-dir.description: SFTP service directory, the total length of absolute path is 128, the length of single directory is 128.

key-name.description: User public key name is a configured public key name of the client. It is a string of 1 to 40 characters.

cipher-alg.description: Configure Encryption algorithms supported for SSHS.

hmac-alg.description: Configure HMAC algorithms supported for SSHS.

dh-group-exchange-sha256.description: Diffie hellman group exchange sha256 algorithm.

dh-group-exchange-sha1.description: Diffie hellman group exchange sha1 algorithm.

dh-min-len.description: Sets the minimum key length for a key exchange algorithm.

stelnet-ipv4-enable.description: User can enable the stelnet IPv4 server.

stelnet-ipv6-enable.description: User can enable the stelnet IPv6 server.

sftp-ipv4-enable.description: User can enable the sftp IPv4 server.

sftp-ipv6-enable.description: User can enable the sftp IPv6 server.

scp-ipv4-enable.description: User can enable the scp IPv4 server.

scp-ipv6-enable.description: User can enable the scp IPv6 server.

snetconf-ipv4-enable.description: User can enable the snetconf IPv4 server.

snetconf-ipv6-enable.description: User can enable the snetconf IPv6 server.

netconf-830-ipv4-enable.description: User can enable the snetconf IPv4 server of port 830.

netconf-830-ipv6-enable.description: User can enable the snetconf IPv6 server of port 830.

tcp-forwarding.description: Enable/disable the TCP port forwarding server.

ipv4-port-number.description: User can change the number of the port monitored by the IPv4 SSH server.

ipv6-port-number.description: User can change the number of the port monitored by the SSH IPv6 server.

sftp-dir.description: Default sftp default directory of SSH user. The specified folder path must exist, otherwise an error will be reported.

x509v3-ssh-rsa.description: Enable/disable X509 RSA public key algorithm.

rsa-sha2-256.description: Enable/disable RSA SHA2-256 public key algorithm.

rsa-sha2-512.description: Enable/disable RSA SHA2-512 public key algorithm.

login-fail-alarm.description: Configure alarm when manager login failed frequently.

upper-limit.description: Login alarm report times, default is 30 times.

lower-limit.description: Login alarm resume times, default is 20 times.

period.description: Login alarm period, default is 5 minutes.

timeout-min.description: The timeout period for a terminal user in minutes.

timeout-sec.description: The timeout period for a terminal user in seconds.

max-sessions.description: User can configure maximum number of clients can be connected to server at any point of time for Netconf service. The maximum value is customized by the PAF file.

ipv4-server-source.description: Configure Specify the source interface policy.

src-interface.description: Specify the source interface name. The specified source interface must exist and an IP address must be configured on the interface.

user-name.description: Name of the user for the current session.
